The paper discusses algorithms in the Congested Clique model and their application to the MapReduce model. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to distributed computing, such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses graph coloring algorithms, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Overall, cs.DC seems to be the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.Distributed Computing.
